<P>A TREATISE Concerning <HI>CONVERSION:</HI> Shewing the <HI>Nature</HI> of Saving CONVERSION To GOD, AND THE <HI>Way</HI> wherein it is wrought; Together with an <HI>Exhortation</HI> to Labour after it. To which is added, A LECTURE-SERMON had at <HI>Bo&s;ton, July</HI> 2, 1719. Wherein the way to know <HI>Sincerity</HI> and <HI>Hypocri&s;y</HI> is cleared up.</P>
<P>By SOLOMON STODDARD, Pa&s;tor of <HI>Northampton.</HI></P>
<P><HI>BOSTON:</HI> Printed by <HI>J. F.</HI> for <HI>D. Henchman,</HI> and Sold at his Shop over again&s;t the Brick Meeting Hou&s;e. 1719.</P>
</DIV1>
