through the knowledge of God and Je&s;us our Lord.</HI> The third time the que&s;tion was put <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> Peter whether he loved Chri&s;t, he an&s;wers with greater a&s;&s;urance; the very propo&s;ing of <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters">e que&s;tion &s;tirred up the working of a &s;pirit <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">f love, and he &s;peaks with very great confi|dence, <HI>Joh.</HI> 21.15, 16, 17. The fir&s;t and &s;e|<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters">nd time he &s;ays, <HI>Yea, Lord, thou knowe&s;t that <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> love thee:</HI> But the third time he &s;peaks with <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters">eate&s;t a&s;&s;urance, <HI>Lord thou knowe&s;t all things-<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters">ou knowe&s;t that I l<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ve thee.</HI> It went great|ly to his heart that his love &s;hould be &s;o of|ten que&s;tioned, and &s;o he was more abundant|ly &s;atisfied in the truth of his love.</P>
